@startuml
title Elastic Resource Capacity Architecture - Vertical Scaling Flow

!include ../../../../../../tooling/styles/plantuml/interaction/sequence-diagram-style.iuml

actor "Cloud Service\nConsumers" as CSC
participant "Cloud Service" as CS
participant "Automated\nScaling Listener" as ASL
participant "Intelligent\nAutomation Engine" as IAE
participant "Hypervisor / VIM" as HV
participant "Resource Pool\n(CPU + RAM sub-pools)" as RP
participant "Virtual Server" as VS

CSC -> CS : (1) send requests
ASL -> CS : (2) monitor runtime\nprocessing

note over IAE
  Intelligent automation engine executes
  scripts containing administration
  workflow logic.
end note

IAE -> IAE : (3) workflow logic\ndeployed
IAE -> RP : (4) prepare allocation\nrequest path

== Demand Increases ==
CSC -> CS : (5) requests increase
ASL -> IAE : (6) signal: execute script
IAE -> HV : (7) request CPU / RAM\n(via VIM or direct)
HV -> RP : retrieve CPU / RAM
HV -> VS : (8) allocate additional\nCPU and RAM
VS --> CS : increased workload\nhandled

note right of VS
  Some virtual servers may require
  rebooting for the dynamic resource
  allocation to take effect.
end note

@enduml
